# Email Utility Module

This module provides functions to send emails with optional HTML formatting and attachments using Python's built-in smtplib and email libraries. It is designed for internal use within the WCAP environment.

## Overview

This module is instantiated using the MailServer class. It requires the vault's internet api key (See Mitch for details).

```
mail_server = MailServer(<Vault-Internet-API-Key>, <SMTP2GO-Password-ID>)
mail_server.send_email("Python@wcap.ca",
           ["user@wcap.ca"],
           "Test Email",
           "This is a plain text email.")
```

The module includes:

- A core function send_email() for sending emails with flexible options.
- Convenience wrappers for specific use cases (email_reporting).
- Deprecated functions for backward compatibility (send_html_email, email_with_attachments).

## Functions

### send_email()

#### Signature

```
send_email(sender: str,
           recipients: list[str],
           subject: str,
           body: str,
           body_type: str = "plain",
           attachments: list[Path] = None
) -> None
```

#### Description

Sends an email with optional HTML content and file attachments.

#### Parameters

- sender (str): Email address of the sender.
- recipients (list[str]): List of recipient email addresses.
- subject (str): Subject line of the email.
- body (str): Email body text.
- body_type (str): "plain" for text or "html" for HTML content. Default is "plain".
- attachments (list[Path]): Optional list of file paths to attach.

#### Behavior

- Creates a MIMEMultipart email container.
- Attaches body as plain text or HTML.
- Adds attachments if provided.
- Sends email via SMTP server mail.wcap.ca on port 25.

### email_reporting()

#### Signature

```
email_reporting(subject: str, body: str) -> None
```

#### Description

Shortcut for sending emails to the reporting team.

#### Parameters

- subject (str): Email subject.
- body (str): Email body.

#### Behavior

- Uses send_email() internally.
- Sender: python@wcap.ca
- Recipient: reporting@wcap.ca

## Usage Examples

### Send a plain text email

```
mail_server = MailServer(<Vault-Internet-API-Key>, <SMTP2GO-Password-ID>)
mail_server.send_email("Python@wcap.ca",
           ["user@wcap.ca"],
           "Test Email",
           "This is a plain text email.")
```

### Send an HTML email

```
mail_server = MailServer(<Vault-Internet-API-Key>, <SMTP2GO-Password-ID>)
mail_server.send_email("Python@wcap.ca",
           ["user@wcap.ca"],
           "HTML Email",
           "`<h1>`Hello`</h1><p>`This is an HTML email.`</p>`",body_type="html"
)
```

### Send email with attachments

```
from pathlib import Path

mail_server = MailServer(<Vault-Internet-API-Key>, <SMTP2GO-Password-ID>)
mail_server.send_email("Python@wcap.ca",
           ["user@wcap.ca"],
           "Report",
           "Please find the attached report.",
           attachments=[Path("report.pdf"), Path("data.csv")])
```

### Send a reporting email
```
mail_server = MailServer(<Vault-Internet-API-Key>, <SMTP2GO-Password-ID>)
mail_server.email_reporting("Reporting report", "This is a log message")
```